DOCKER NOTES
-----------------
IMAGE  BUILD 
1) Launch Docker Engine
2) docker image build -t <image_name> .
3) docker image inspect <image_name>
4) docker image ls

TO RUN CONTAINER
5) docker run --name <CONTAINER NAME> -it <DOCKER HUB USER ACCT>/<image_name>:latest
(interactive terminal)

(with port mapping and background mode)
docker run --name <CONTAINER NAME> -p port:port -d <image name>
docker run --name my_ip -p 5000:5000 -d show_ip_5


CONTAINER STOP+REMOVAL
1) docker stop <container_name>
and if needed: 
2) docker rm <container_name>

--OR--
to do both 1) and 2)
3) docker rm -f <container_name>


IMAGE PULL
1) docker login
2) docker pull <example_user>/<image_name>:<tag>

IMAGE PUSH 
1) docker login
2) docker image tag <local_image_name> <example_user>/<repo_image_name>:<tag>
3) docker image push <example_user>/<image_name>:<tag>


PUSH TO GCR
1) gcloud init
2)gcloud auth configure-docker
3) docker build -t <image_name>:latest .
4) docker tag [SOURCE_IMAGE] gcr.io/[PROJECT-ID]/[IMAGE]
5) docker push gcr.io/[PROJECT-ID]/[IMAGE]

docker run -it --rm -e <MY_ENV_VAR=my_value> -v <HOST PATH>:<PATH IN CONTAINER> <IMAGE NAME>

-it is interactive terminal (for the container)
--rm removes the container after it closes

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DOCKER GAME - Containerization(WINDOWS):

1. Use python 3.9 Image with no dependancies on your docker file; Copy a Graphical game of your choice from Theos link into your app.py
>>(BUILD-THE-DOCKER-FILE)
docker build -t <LIZZO-GOES-HERE> .

2. Install VcXsrv Windows X Server (Xserver)

3. XLaunch in windows search -- Change Display Number to 0 Change nothing else.

4. RUN-IT
winpty docker run -it --rm -e DISPLAY=host.docker.internal:0.0 -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix <CHANGE-LIZZO-HERE>

5. SHUT-IT - Power off docker first using the power button on docker
>> <INPUT BELOW COMMAND IN YOUR TERMINAL>
wsl --shutdown 

6. Close Xlaunch on the system Tray.
